\pard\f0\fs28   {\b S. atrovirens} Willd.,{\i  Enum. Pl. Horti Berol.} 79 (1809), native of North America, is like {\b 1} but with spikelets in fascicles of 8-20 at the apices of the ultimate rays, usually brownish-red glumes and perianth-bristles smooth below; it has been reported frequently as a casual in C. Europe and N.E. France and is perhaps becoming naturalized.
