\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. S. radicans} Schkuhr, {\i Ann. Bot.} ({\i Usteri}) {\b 4}: 48 (1793). Like {\b 1} but stems caespitose; long, procumbent non-flowering shoots present which root and form new plants at their apices; spikelets 3-8 mm, lanceolate, ovoid-lanceolate or elliptical, acute, usually solitary at apices of ultimate rays; glumes not mucronulate; perianth-bristles 2-3 times as long as nut, smooth or with only a few retrorse hairs towards apex, flexuous.{\i  Damp places. From S. Norway and Finland southwards to the Vosges, N. Italy and C. Romania.} Au Cz Fe Ga Ge Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W) Su.
