\pard\f0\fs28   {\b S}. × {\b carinatus} Sm.,{\i  Engl. Bot.}{\b  28}: 1983 (1809) ({\b 4} × {\b 8}; incl. {\i S. kalmussii} Ascherson, Abromeit & Graebner), occurs mainly in C. & N.W. Europe; it has the general appearance of{\b  4}, but the stems are terete below and trigonous above the middle, the nuts are plano-convex, and the glumes often have some red papillae.
